---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Entry from '../components/Entry.astro';
import Media from '../components/Media.astro';
---

<Base title="Trajectory — Sebastian Correa-Gallego" description="Education, milestones, recognitions, and future direction in the current stage of my academic trajectory.">
  <header class="page-intro">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="page-intro__eyebrow">Trajectory</span>
      <h1>The path so far, and the kind of biological work I am trying to build toward</h1>
      <p class="page-intro__lede">
        This page is less about listing every activity and more about showing how my scientific
        questions have become more coherent during undergraduate training.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container container--wide trajectory-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="section-head reveal">
          <p class="section-head__eyebrow">Orientation</p>
          <span class="section-head__line"></span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="section-title reveal">A trajectory increasingly organized by natural systems, gradients, and biological constraint.</h2>
        <p class="section-lede reveal">
          My academic path has not been linear in topic, but it has become more coherent with
          time. What now links the work is not a single organism or method. It is a way of asking
          how living systems organize themselves when conditions are limiting.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal">
          The route I want is not purely molecular and not anti-quantitative. It is closer to a
          contemporary naturalist orientation: one that takes natural history, ecology,
          physiology, and rigorous analysis seriously at the same time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <Media
          placeholder="cave-deep"
          aspectRatio="12 / 7"
          label="Future field and laboratory photographs will live here"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <p class="section-head__eyebrow">Education</p>
        <span class="section-head__line"></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Where the foundation of this trajectory has been built.</h2>
      <p class="section-lede reveal">
        Biology at Universidad EAFIT has been the institutional base from which my interests in
        microbes, gradients, and natural systems have become more coherent and more research-led.
      </p>
      <Entry title="Universidad EAFIT" date="2022 – 2026 (expected)" role="B.Sc. in Biology">
        <p>
          Undergraduate training in biology with sustained involvement in microbiology,
          environmental systems, and research-led learning. My thesis centers on cultivable
          microbial community structure in a tropical volcaniclastic cave.
        </p>
      </Entry>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <p class="section-head__eyebrow">Milestones</p>
        <span class="section-head__line"></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Experiences that gave the profile more shape and direction.</h2>
      <p class="section-lede reveal">
        These are the moments that widened the scale of the work: from student initiative, to
        project support, to a broader international research context.
      </p>

      <Entry title="Student Director" date="Oct 2023 – Present" role="Research Group on Microbiology and Astrobiology · Universidad EAFIT">
        <p>
          Coordinate a student-led group devoted to microbiology, astrobiology, scientific
          discussion, and undergraduate initiative-building.
        </p>
      </Entry>

      <Entry title="Research Monitor" date="Jul 2024 – Dec 2024" role="Universidad EAFIT">
        <p>
          Supported the project <em>Positioning of Microorganisms as Fundamental Actors for the
          Maintenance of Andean Forests</em> through systematization, communication, and written
          scientific support.
        </p>
      </Entry>

      <Entry title="Visiting Student Intern" date="Aug 2025 – Jan 2026" role="ECSO Lab, Purdue University">
        <p>
          Expanded my training into evolutionary cell biology and proteomics-linked reasoning,
          adding a second scale to my scientific profile while keeping continuity with the
          broader problem of biological organization under limitation.
        </p>
      </Entry>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <p class="section-head__eyebrow">Recognition</p>
        <span class="section-head__line"></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">External signs that the work has already started to register.</h2>
      <p class="section-lede reveal">
        These recognitions are not the center of the story, but they do matter as early signals
        that the trajectory is gaining definition and support.
      </p>

      <Entry title="Research proposal presentation" date="2024" role="2nd Symposium of Biology · Universidad EAFIT" note="Second place">
        <p>
          Awarded for presenting my undergraduate research proposal in a competitive academic
          setting.
        </p>
      </Entry>

      <Entry title="Undergraduate scholarship" date="2022" role="Comfama and Fundación Fraternidad Medellín">
        <p>
          Early institutional support that helped anchor the beginning of my undergraduate path.
        </p>
      </Entry>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--tight">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <p class="section-head__eyebrow">Looking ahead</p>
        <span class="section-head__line"></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">The intellectual shape of what I want the next stage to preserve.</h2>
      <p class="section-lede reveal">
        I want the next phase of training to deepen rigor without narrowing range too early.
        What matters most is keeping ecology, evolution, physiology, and natural systems in the
        same frame, rather than forcing them apart.
      </p>
      <div class="future-grid reveal-stagger">
        <article class="future-card reveal">
          <h3 class="future-card__title">What I want to preserve</h3>
          <p class="future-card__text">
            Range. I do not want to reduce my profile to only one method or one biological
            scale. I want field, theory, and analysis to remain in contact.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="future-card reveal">
          <h3 class="future-card__title">What I want to deepen</h3>
          <p class="future-card__text">
            Stronger quantitative reasoning, richer ecological framing, and a more mature
            understanding of how microbial and cellular systems negotiate constraint.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="future-card reveal">
          <h3 class="future-card__title">What comes next</h3>
          <p class="future-card__text">
            Graduate research environments where microbial ecology, evolution, physiology, and
            natural systems can be studied without forcing them into separate intellectual boxes.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
